	<section_number>18.2-25</section_number>
	<catch_line>Attempts to commit Class 1 felony offenses; how punished</catch_line>
	<text>
		If any person attempts to commit an offense that is punishable as a Class 1 felony, he is guilty of a Class 2 felony.
	</text>
	<history>Code 1950, § 18.1-16; 1960, c. 358; 1975, cc. 14, 15; 1985, c. 280; 2021, Sp. Sess. I, cc. 344, 345.</history>
</law>
